quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  25,12,"When it sights them from a distant place, they will hear it raging and roaring"
  25,13,"And when they are cast into a narrow place in it, bound together [in chains], they will pray for [their own] annihilation"
  25,14,"[They will be told:] ‘Do not pray for a single annihilation today, but pray for many annihilations!’"
  25,15,"Say, ‘Is that better, or the everlasting paradise promised to the Godwary, which will be their reward and destination?’"
  25,16,"There they will have whatever they wish, abiding [forever]—a promise [much] besought, [binding] on your Lord"
  25,17,"On the day that He will muster them and those whom they worship besides Allah, He will say, ‘Was it you who led astray these servants of Mine, or did they themselves stray from the way?’"
  25,18,"They will say, ‘Immaculate are You! It does not behoove us to take any wali in Your stead! But You provided for them and their fathers until they forgot the Reminder, and they were a ruined lot.’"
  25,19,"So they will certainly impugn you in what you say, and you will neither be able to circumvent [punishment] nor find help, and whoever of you does wrong, We shall make him taste a terrible punishment"
  25,20,"We did not send any apostles before you but that they indeed ate food and walked in marketplaces. We have made you a [means of] test for one another, [to see] if you will be patient and steadfast, and your Lord is all-seeing"